The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, delivered remarks at the sixth meeting of the National Space Council, held at the Steven F. Udvar-Hazy Center in Chantilly, Virginia. Pence highlighted the progress made by the Trump administration in revitalizing American leadership in space, including the commitment to return to the moon and prioritize crewed missions to the lunar surface. He also emphasized the importance of establishing a permanent presence on the moon as a stepping stone to Mars. Pence discussed the administration's support for NASA and the private space industry, as well as the establishment of the United States Space Force. He concluded by calling on all attendees to share the story of American leadership in space and inspire the world.